   - **Input Format:** 
     - Line 1: `N M` (number of tasks, number of dependencies)
     - Line 2: `N` distinct task names (space-separated)
     - Next `M` lines: `A B` (A must be completed before B)
   - **Output Format:** Space-separated task names in build order, or `IMPOSSIBLE` if a cycle exists.
   - **Constraints:**
     - Deterministic build order
     - Lexicographically smallest task name when multiple are available
     - Time complexity: O((N + M) log N) or better
     - Implement own binary heap/priority queue (no repeated sorting of available set)
